Class BraceletList<T>

java.lang.Object
bracelet.Bracelet1<T>
bracelet.BraceletList<T>
Type Parameters:
T - The type of elements in this bracelet
All Implemented Interfaces:
Bracelet<T>, BraceletKernel<T>
public class BraceletList<T> extends Bracelet1<T> implements Bracelet<T>
A secondary implementation of Bracelet that allows for more flexibility with adding, removing, and cycling through the bracelet.
Author:
David Cooney

      public T removeEntry(T x)
      Description copied from interface: Bracelet
      Removes requested object from the Bracelet. Bracelet allows for duplicate elements to be contained with itself. When calling upon removeEntry(x) to remove an element with multiple appearances in this, the instance of the element closest to the front of this will be removed.

      Requires |this| is greater than 0

      Ensures this = [#this with x removed]
